# AWKIT Project Rule

AWKIT / WebFlow Studio is an offline-capable Windows desktop app for visual Playwright web automation.

Before editing:
- Read `AGENTS.md`.
- Read `docs/ai/README.md` if present.
- Read `docs/ai/CURRENT_STATE.md`.
- Read `docs/ai/HANDOFF.md` before implementation work.
- Read only task-relevant extra docs.

Rules:
- Keep changes minimal and scoped.
- Do not rewrite unrelated code.
- Preserve offline-first behavior.
- Do not add CDN, remote font, runtime internet, or cloud dependencies.
- Do not rename `window.playwrightFlowStudio`.
- Do not store mutable runtime data under `resources/` or `app.asar`.
- Do not copy secrets into code, logs, docs, or tests.

After meaningful changes:
- Run the relevant verification commands.
- Update `docs/ai/TASK_LOG.md`.
- Update `docs/ai/CURRENT_STATE.md` only if project state changed.
- Update `docs/ai/HANDOFF.md` if work is paused or handed off.
